      {
        "paragraph_index": 2,
        "text": "What this means\n- Breadth of data: Cu(II) has the most extensive complexation dataset in SRD‑46 (by far more β definitions, ligand diversity, and measurements than Fe(III)/Fe(II)). Fe(III) is better covered than Fe(II), and Cu(I) is comparatively sparse.\n- Practical implication: For side-by-side stability comparisons, Cu(II) offers the richest set of matched-condition constants; Fe(III) also has substantial coverage, while Fe(II) and especially Cu(I) may require broader condition tolerances or more targeted ligands.",
